  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "sticky-overview-06",
      "name": "Overview",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [-240, -420],
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ðŸ“Š Email Engagement Tracker\n\n**What this workflow does:**\n1. Listens for `email.opened` and `email.clicked` events from Resend\n2. Formats each event into a structured row of data\n3. Appends the engagement event to a Google Sheet for analytics and tracking\n\n**Data logged per event:**\n- Timestamp\n- Event type (opened / clicked)\n- Recipient email\n- Resend Email ID\n- Email subject\n- Click URL (for click events)\n\n**Use cases:**\n- Email campaign performance analytics\n- Lead scoring (contacts who click = hot leads)\n- Re-engagement targeting (identify who opened but never clicked)\n- Deliverability monitoring dashboards\n\n> Inspired by Gmail + Google Sheets email tracking workflows, rebuilt for Resend's structured webhook event system.",
        "height": 440,
        "width": 580,
        "color": 1
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "sticky-setup-06",
      "name": "Setup Instructions",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [340, -420],
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## âš™ï¸ Setup Required\n\n**Step 1 â€“ Resend Webhook Signing Secret credential**\nCreate a \"Resend Webhook Signing Secret\" credential in n8n. Add it to the Resend Trigger node.\n\n**Step 2 â€“ Register the webhook in Resend**\nActivate the workflow, copy the **production webhook URL** from the Resend Trigger node, then register it in your [Resend Webhooks dashboard](https://resend.com/webhooks).\nSelect: `email.opened` and `email.clicked`.\n\n**Step 3 â€“ Google Sheets credential**\nCreate a Google Sheets OAuth2 credential in n8n. Add it to the Google Sheets node.\n\n**Step 4 â€“ Create your tracking spreadsheet**\nCreate a Google Sheet with these column headers in row 1:\n```\nTimestamp | Event | Recipient | Email ID | Subject | Clicked URL\n```\n\n**Step 5 â€“ Connect the spreadsheet**\nIn the Google Sheets node, select your spreadsheet and sheet (or paste the Sheet ID).\n\n> ðŸ’¡ Use **Test mode** in the Resend Trigger while building â€” click \"Listen for test event\" to capture live events in the n8n editor.",
        "height": 540,
        "width": 560,
        "color": 3
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "sticky-schema-06",
      "name": "Google Sheet Schema",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [-240, 400],
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ðŸ“‹ Required Google Sheet Columns\n\nCreate a sheet with these headers (exact names, row 1):\n\n| A | B | C | D | E | F |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `Timestamp` | `Event` | `Recipient` | `Email ID` | `Subject` | `Clicked URL` |\n\n`Clicked URL` will be empty for `email.opened` events â€” only populated for `email.clicked` events.",
        "height": 200,
        "width": 560,
        "color": 4
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "n06-trigger",
      "name": "Resend Engagement Events",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-resend.resendTrigger",
